                    EARTH SCIENCE > ATMOSPHERE > ATMOSPHERIC RADIATION > SHORTWAVE RADIATION

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    Shortwave radiation is radiation at wavelengths shorter than 4
microns. Sometimes called the solar radiation. Usually radiation in the
visible and near-infrared wavelengths. 
                
                

                

                
